I'm not opposed to the idea of a story being carried across multiple skips, but I really wish there was more information in this article about who Brandt is, and what Sector H is for, seeing as they are both necessary components to the event instigated here. From a tonal standpoint, I'm bothered by a Foundation agent acting so blasé about what sounds like a potential breach. It's hard to imagine any workplace where a naked man in an owl mask would be brushed off as drunken hijinks; at a Foundation site, it seems more likely to result in a task force being deployed, than a  type of comment. What is, or was, Sector H, that this kind of activity doesn't result in a higher level of alarm? Never-the-less, there's definitely something or interest to me going on here, and I hope reading the linked articles gives me more than what this little glimpse offered.







